item.paragraph: (NM Myocardial Perf SPECT Mult Study) Reason For Exam: CHF/DYSPNEA ON EXCERSION/CHEST PAIN/FATIGUE

paragraph.content:
CLINICAL INFORMATION: CHF/DYSPNEA ON EXERTION/CHEST PAIN/FATIGUE. Carotid artery stenosis. Congestive heart failure. Hyperlipidemia. Hypertension. Left ventricular hypertrophy. Diabetes.
EXAMINATION: NM MYOCARDIAL PERF SPECT MULT STUDY, 2020-11-04 8:30 AM, NM200009553
COMPARISON: None
RADIOPHARMACEUTICAL: 8.9 millicuries technetium 99m tetrofosmin IV for the rest exam. 38 millicuries technetium 99m tetrofosmin IV for the stress exam.
FINDINGS: Patient underwent pharmacologic stress with 0.4 mg LexiScan IV. Heart rate changed from 85-103 beats per minute. Blood pressure changed from 148/97-161/88. Patient's reported height and weight are 5 feet 2 inches, 230 pounds.
Supine post stress SPECT images and resting SPECT images are obtained. Patient was unable to lay prone for additional imaging. Study is reviewed at the workstation. MIP images demonstrate significant soft tissue attenuation over the left ventricle due to overlying breast tissue. There is a mild shift in soft tissue positioning between stress and rest images.
Supine post stress images demonstrate mildly diminished activity involving proximal anterior wall. No definite reversibility.
Mildly diminished activity involving the distal inferior wall and the apex. No definite reversibility.
No other defects. No reversible defects.
Wall motion: Gated resting and post stress images demonstrate no focal wall motion abnormalities.
Ejection fraction: LVEF is 44% after stress. Post stress end diastolic volume is 110 mL.
IMPRESSION:
1. Negative for ischemia.
2. LVEF 44%.
Procedure performed with dual-headed camera and completed using appropriate computer software.
"This patient may be released based on the guidelines established in the state Division of Radiological Health regulations, Release of Patients Containing Radioactive Drugs or Implants."
